FBIS3-34528 "drnes027_v_94003" FBIS-NES-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 Pakistan Bhutto Sends `National Reconciliation' Message to Sharif BK0802101494 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service in English 0800 GMT 8 Feb 94 BK0802101494 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, has sent a message to the opposition leader in the National Assembly, Mr. Mohammad Nawaz Sharif. The message was delivered by the federal minister for water and power, Malik Ghulam Mustafa Khar, in Lahore this morning. Later talking to newsmen, the minister said that the message was in the overall context of national reconciliation. Replying to questions, he said the message was reflective of the prime minister's keen desire for national reconciliation. He said the present government does not want to enter into any sort of confrontation with anyone.
